criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18-65 years old;

          -  Documented HIV infection;

          -  No history of gastrointestinal diseases;

          -  Good adherence and promise to follow-up;

          -  Ability to provide informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Administration of antibiotics, probiotics, or prebiotics or experience of diarrhea
             within the previous 3 months;

          -  Administration of anti-inflammatory drugs, corticosteroids, immunosuppressive drugs,
             immunomodulator within the previous 3 months;

          -  Severe organ dysfunction;

          -  Pregnancy or breastfeeding.
